# Velora Bundles — Master Project Rules

## What this project is
Velora Bundles is a Shopify App Store app that lets merchants create product bundles, volume discounts, and BOGO deals to increase Average Order Value (AOV). Built by a solo developer. Simple, clean, affordable — competing against Kaching Bundles and Fast Bundle.

## Tech stack — never deviate
- **Framework**: React Router v7 (formerly Remix) — Shopify's official framework
- **Language**: TypeScript strict mode — no `any` types, no implicit types
- **UI**: Shopify Polaris web components — NEVER use raw HTML or Tailwind in admin UI
- **Admin embed**: Shopify App Bridge — all navigation via App Bridge
- **ORM**: Prisma — never write raw SQL queries
- **Database**: PostgreSQL (production), SQLite (local dev only)
- **Cache**: Redis via ioredis — cache all analytics, bundle configs, sessions
- **API**: Shopify GraphQL Admin API ONLY — REST API is deprecated, never use it
- **Discount engine**: Shopify Functions (TypeScript) — NOT Shopify Scripts (deprecated June 2026)
- **Storefront**: Theme App Extension (Liquid + vanilla JS) — no React on storefront
- **Payments**: Shopify Billing API — never charge merchants directly
- **Hosting**: Railway (Node.js + PostgreSQL + Redis)
- **Error tracking**: Sentry (@sentry/node)
- **Emails**: Resend (transactional emails)

